Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Mornye, Abby has a... strange question.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Can the Submerged Tunnel project different types of holograms?

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Like, say… a swarm of Dragons of Dirge? Or make the entire length of the tunnel a Path of the Inferno?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I wasn't part of the Submerged Tunnel project. To answer accurately would require a site survey and access to blueprints, construction logs, operational data…

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I recall that the tunnel runs from Bjartr Woods to Sundermere. I'm near Bjartr Woods now. I could come help you if you need it.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Aren't you on sick leave??

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: ...On an expedition. For a project.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Don't worry. Dr. Herssen says my post-Overclocking symptoms are mostly recovered. Now, I just need to stay in a good mood.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: And… making research progress puts me in a very good mood.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: (Confused Abby)

Options.PlotLineKey: What you need right now is rest.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: What you need right now is rest.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Once your expedition is complete, meet me by the tunnel. We need to talk.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: (Fierce)

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: (Puppy dog eyes)

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: ...All right.

Dialogues.Speaker: SystemTip
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: You receive a WavesLine message from Mornye.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Have you noticed anything special about the night sky tonight?

Options.PlotLineKey: Indeed, I even took a snap of them just now.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: The pattern formed by the stars hanging above us?

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Indeed, I even took a snap of them just now.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Oh, you've found one of the star charts for the stargazing event.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Stargazing event?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: It's an event held by Startorch Academy to inspire the explorer within every student.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: As you know, the night sky of Lahai-Roi is a collection of light dots created by the Sky Projection Array. That gives the Academy the liberty to manipulate it as we see fit.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: By reimagining the night sky, we inspire the students to explore.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Students are rewarded for collecting all of the star charts. Would you be interested in giving it a try?

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Of course I'm in.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Alright, please contact me once you've found them all. I hope you enjoy our stargazing event.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Good Luck

Dialogues.Speaker: SystemTip
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: You receive a WavesLine message from Mornye.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I've found all the star charts for the event.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Star Pattern 1

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Star Pattern 2

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Star Pattern 3

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Star Pattern 4

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Like

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Hmm, they match up. Congratulations! You've completed the stargazing event!

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: If you've got the time, you can claim your reward from the Spacetrek Observatory. I'll be waiting for you.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey:
Hello, I'm Mornye from the Spacetrek Collective.
Sorry to bother you, but I need a clear report on what happened during the Hyvatia Detector's failure, so I can lead a repair plan. Since you and Lynae were the only witnesses on-site, I'd like to meet with both of you tomorrow.
If you're willing, please respond with "I accept."

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I accept.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Sure. Where?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Thank you. We'll meet at the Academy dormitory at nine o'clock tomorrow morning. I'll be there on time.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Besides that, I want to ask about something unrelated to work.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: During the Voidworm's attack on Startorch Academy, were you injured? If you experience any frequency issues again, we can help. I'll handle your case myself.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I'm fine. The frequency loss has stopped for now, but I appreciate you checking in.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: There is one thing... It's a bit strange, though...

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Would it be possible to bring some delicious Spacetrek snacks to the meeting?

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Sorry. It's Abby's idea.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: If it's inappropriate for a work meeting, don't worry about it.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: ...No, it's fine.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I'll make a note of it.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Mornye, where are you?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Has the feast finished already?

Options.PlotLineKey: I couldn't find you. I was worried.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Yes, it is.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I'm sorry if I worried you.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I couldn't find you. I was worried.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: But... I'm the professor, and you're the student. It should be my place to worry about you.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I thought I was your mentor?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: ...I see. Sorry to make you worry.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: (Attachment: a picture of the night sky)

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I'm here. Right beneath the 13th planet of the Norma constellation.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I'm afraid I'm unable to move at the moment. Please, I'll need you to come find me here.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Look, Mentor, the rain and Helios's light are woven together.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Photo: Starward Riseway in a sunshower.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Beyond Lahai-Roi, you sometimes get sunshowers like this. The reason being...

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I probably shouldn't go into that. I only messaged you to share this photo.

Options.PlotLineKey: It's got something to do with water vapor and evaporation.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Rain, Helios's light, and the Starward Riseway piercing the clouds.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Combined, they create a distinct and extraordinary spectacle.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Yes... It's rather unique. I really enjoy it.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I believe the cause of such spectacle has to do with the intensity of solar radiation, is it not?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Ah, yes, there could be a variety of reasons, as nature's complexity is something no simulation can replicate.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Of course, we won't just stop there. We wish to go beyond it.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Just like the Exostrider in the past, illuminating the way and reaching ever farther.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: But do make sure to take a break every now and then, Mentor.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Abby's Life: Flower Delivery

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Abby's Life: Cheers

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: A meteor shower with the Observatory in the background.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I came to the Spacetrek Observatory to collect some data, Mentor.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I didn't expect to stumble upon a sight like this.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: So the Sky Projection Array now includes data on meteor showers.

Options.PlotLineKey: That only came after the reconstruction.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: They added new control modules and expanded the Weather Simulation data after the reconstruction project.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I see, so the Projection Ring emits signals to create the weather simulation. Is that correct?

Options.PlotLineKey: Right, for now, it only affects local areas.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Yes, the array itself is divided into several sectors.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: The control signals for the Weather Simulation can only alter the array in specific areas.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Having contributed to the reconstruction personally, you just couldn't resist sharing its secrets, could you?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: You really are a passionate researcher.

Options.PlotLineKey: Maybe someone rubbed off on me.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Maybe someone rubbed off on me.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Oh?

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: I see. Since I've been interacting with you more often lately, our speech patterns have begun to converge.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: That… actually makes me quite happy.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: By the way, Dhalifa said you were the one who sent the signal for the simulated meteor shower.

Dialogues.Speaker: Mornye
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Thank you, Mentor. This view is truly breathtaking.

Dialogues.Speaker: {PlayerName}
Dialogues.PlotLineKey: Abby's Life: Flower Delivery
